=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Klank_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 350 Hz, featuring punchy attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: sustained
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 350.2374
  harmonic_decay_rate: 4.6193
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0626
  pitch_clarity: 11.8587
  inharmonicity: 0.2274
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.1704
  resonance_freq: 1098.1934

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Klank Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Klank.html
// Tags: Klank, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
(
{
Klank.ar([ // the multichannel-expansion
    `[[500, 1078, 1201.5, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 0.5, 0.3]], // left channel
    `[[700, 1071, 1053, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]] // right channel
    ], Impulse.ar([1.5, 1.875], 0, 0.1))
}.play
);

// expanding specs within the parameter array
{ Klank.ar(`[[[800, 6000], 1071, [1153, 8000], 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]], Impulse.ar([2, 3], 0, 0.1)) }.play;
